Nigeria’s Federal Capital Territory, Abuja is set to host the fourth edition of the African Track Cycling Championship. Nigeria and 14 other countries are expected to participate in the Championship which will take place inside the Velodrome of the Moshood Abiola National Stadium, Abuja from today through Sunday.   Dembele agrees new 2-year Barcelona contract     Osimhen returns to Napoli for preseason     Falode recalls Ukaigwe’s giant strides as stakeholders marks…   Ahead of the Championship, the Honourable Minister of Youth and Sports Development, Hon. Sunday Dare alongside other top Ministry officials and the President of the Cycling Federation of Nigeria (CFN), Giandomenico Massari today visited the venue of the event. He welcomed them to the tournament, charging them to put up their best while also assuring them of a hitch-free competition. A delegation from the Confederation of African Cycling(CAC) led by its president Dr Mohamed Waguih Azzam later paid a courtesy visit on the Sports Minister. The participating teams are Burundi, Morocco, South Africa, Egypt, Algeria, Cote D’Ivoire, Togo, Ghana, Burkina Faso, Tunisia, Niger Republic, Benin Republic, Guinea and Botswana and host, Nigeria.